                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.74/56: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-01-08T22:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 8, 1921—10 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 8—3:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>14. Legation’s 467, December 28, 4 p.m. Contract<note n="3" xml:id="d372fn3">For
                        text of the contract, see <hi rend="italic">List of Contracts of American
                            Nationals with the Chinese Government</hi>, etc., annex VIII (Government
                        Printing Office, 1925).</note> signed today in the presence of Legation
                    representatives, text by the next pouch. Supplementary letter provides that
                    contract becomes effective upon ratification by the company. As the contract
                    provides for overseas communications, Legation considers it to be removed from
                    the scope of the consortium. Attempting maintain secrecy pending
                    ratification.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
